ensional manifolds -- tSection 18. Loops on 1-manifolds having a locally compact left translation group -- tSection 19. Topological loops on 2-dimensional manifolds -- tSection 20. Topological loops on tori -- tSection 21. Topological loops on the cylinder and on the plane -- tSection 22. The hyperbolic plane loop and its isotopism class -- tSection 23. Two-dimensional loops having a 3-dimensional solvable Lie group as their group generated by the left translations -- tSection 24. 2-dimensional Bol loops having a 4-dimensional Lie group as the group generated by their left translations -- tSection 25. Classification of differentiable 2-dimensional Bol loops -- tSection 26. Collineation groups of 4-dimensional Bol nets -- tSection 27. Strongly left alternative plane left A-loops -- tSection 28. 2-dimensional loops having a Lie group as the group generated by all translations -- tSection 29. Multiplicative loops of locally compact connected quasifields -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn this book the theory of binary systems is considered as a part of group theory and, in particular, within the framework of Lie groups. The novelty is the consequent treatment of topological and differentiable loops as topological and differentiable sections in Lie groups. The interplay of methods and tools from group theory, differential geometry and topology, symmetric spaces, topological geometry, and the theory of foliations is what gives a special flavour to the results presented in this book. It is the first monograph devoted to the study of global loops. So far books on differentiable loops deal with local loops only. This theory can only be used partially for the theory of global loops since non-associative local structures have, in general, no global forms. The text is addressed to researchers in non-associative algebra and foundations of geometry. It should prove enlightening to a broad range of readers, including mathematicians working in group theory, the theory of Lie groups, in differential and topological geometry, and in algebraic groups. The authors have produced a text that is suitable not only for a graduate course, but also for selfstudy in the subjectby interested graduate students. Moreover, the material presented can be used for lectures and seminars in algebra, topological algebra and geometry.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aLie groups. 0aLoops (Group theory). 4aLie-Gruppe. 4aLoop. 7aMATHEMATICS / General.2bisacsh1 aStrambach, Karl, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Expositions in Mathematics Backlist eBook Packagez9783110494969oZDB-23-EXM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Mathematics 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023847108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Mathematics - 2000 - 2014z9783110637205oZDB-23-GMA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-DITION 2: BEST OF MATHEMATICS, PHYSICSz9783110306569oZDB-23-DBI0 cprintz978311017010840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311090058340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110900583423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110900583/original  a978-3-11-023847-1  DGBA Backlist Mathematics 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MTPY  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MTPY  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DBI  aZDB